Turns out, I was supposed to vacuum my entire house, take everything off of the floor, wash all of the sheets and all of the pet bedding while it was being treated, and then not vacuum for another twenty four hours. They also failed to tell me beforehand that my cat was not supposed to return to the house for two days! So, I vacuumed when I got home last night, for an hour-and-a-half, and brought my cat into the apartment, because nobody told me otherwise. So I just completely negated the whole process by vacuuming, but they won't be able to come back for another ten days!!! I have huge bites all over my ankles and legs, and I now have to figure out some place to keep my cat for two days while it gets treated again!<br>
I talked to the vet today, and she said it's the worst flea season they've seen in years. The best part is, my cat is an indoor cat. He never comes in contact with other animals. The only time he goes outside is to sit on our second-story balcony.<br>
I hate fleas!!! I'm walking around all day scratching my legs, and it sucks! I can't really find anything that's a good repellant that I can wear all day without smelling like bug spray either. Any ideas? I'm willing to try ANYTHING at this point. <p><br>
